{"segment_id": "00093", "page_num": 93, "segment": "and makes it happen. Your role is to remain keenly aware,\npatiently expectant, and open to all possibilities.16\n\nThe amazing thing about New Thought is that it is always\npresented as if it were new! And no matter how many times the\nsame ideas are repeated, they are received by many listeners with\nfresh nods of armation. These ritual recitations obviously tap into\na deep human capacity to believe that intensely focused desire is\nmagically rewarded.\n\nrecommended as approaches\n\nI do not know whether meditation and other inward journeys\nperfect the human soul. But I do know that believing that rays come\nout of your head and change the physical world, and that by\nthinking only of success you can become a success, are forms of\npsychosis and cannot be\nto\nmanagement or strategy. All analysis starts with the consideration of\nwhat may happen, including unwelcome events. I would not care to\ny in an aircraft designed by people who focused only on an image\nof a ying airplane and never considered modes of failure.\nNevertheless, the doctrine that one can impose one’s visions and\ndesires on the world by the force of thought alone retains a\npowerful appeal to many people. Its acceptance displaces critical\nthinking and good strategy.", "source_file": "GOOD-STRATEGY-BAD-STRATEGY.pdf", "extraction_method": "pdfminer", "ocr_used": false, "has_table": false, "chapter_num": "1", "chapter_title": ", “Good Strategy Is Unexpected,” and chapter 2,", "section_num": "2.0", "section_title": "businesses. The term “Web 2.0” purportedly referred to a", "l1_summary": "Your role is to remain keenly aware,\npatiently expectant, and open to all possibilities.16 The amazing thing about New Thought is that it is always\npresented as if it were new! And no matter how many times the\nsame ideas are repeated, they are received by many listeners with\nfresh nods of armation.", "l2_summary": "Your role is to remain keenly aware,\npat