ous with a superior rate of prot.", "source_file": "GOOD-STRATEGY-BAD-STRATEGY.pdf", "extraction_method": "pdfminer", "ocr_used": false, "has_table": false, "chapter_num": "1", "chapter_title": ", “Good Strategy Is Unexpected,” and chapter 2,", "section_num": "2.0", "section_title": "businesses. The term “Web 2.0” purportedly referred to a", "l1_summary": "Combining any two\ncompanies sums their cash ows---that’s arithmetic. “Telecom Italia,” I said, “already has substantial cash ow. I just don’t see any\n‘economies of mass’ in combining these cash ows.”", "l2_summary": "The combined company will have much\ngreater cash ow.” Combining any two\ncompanies sums their cash ows---that’s arithmetic. It is not an\nargument for why a specic deal is worth the price. “Telecom Italia,” I said, “already has substantial cash ow. I just don’t see any\n‘economies of mass’ in combining these cash ows.” He said,\n“With more cash ow you can do a bigger deal.” Then he left the\nroom.", "prev_page": {"page_num": 179, "segment_id": "00179"}, "next_page": {"page_num": 181, "segment_id": "00181"}, "extended_fields": {"has_code": false, "has_formulas": false, "has_diagram": false, "has_list": false, "has_citations": false, "key_terms": ["cash", "deal", "just", "economies", "mass", "companies", "will", "larger", "company", "argument"], "content_type": "theory", "domain": "management", "complexity": "intermediate", "companies": ["Telecom Italia", "Cable & Wireless"], "people": ["Joseph Silver", "Gianmario Rossignolo"], "products": [], "technologies": [], "frameworks": [], "methodologies": [], "programming_languages": [], "has_best_practices": false, "has_antipatterns": true, "has_instructions": false, "has_metrics": false, "metrics": [], "has_case_study": true, "case_study_company": null, "tools_mentioned": [], "topics": ["merger and acquisition", "cash flow management", "company valuation"], "key_concepts": ["economies of mass", "cash flow analysis", "board decision making"], "problem_state