inkers. Joseph Addison, Alexander Pope, and Jonathan Swift held\nforth at Buttons.", "source_file": "GOOD-STRATEGY-BAD-STRATEGY.pdf", "extraction_method": "pdfminer", "ocr_used": false, "has_table": false, "chapter_num": "1", "chapter_title": ", “Good Strategy Is Unexpected,” and chapter 2,", "section_num": "2.0", "section_title": "businesses. The term “Web 2.0” purportedly referred to a", "l1_summary": "Why should they drink “bad” coee and not\nenjoy the pleasures of an espresso latte in a social setting? He returned to Seattle and explained his idea to the two owners\nof the company he worked for---the Starbucks Coee Company. When Howard Schultz pitched his proposal to the owners of\nStarbucks, the...", "l2_summary": "Why should they drink “bad” coee and not\nenjoy the pleasures of an espresso latte in a social setting? Italian espresso\nexperience could be re-created in America and the public would embrace\nit. He returned to Seattle and explained his idea to the two owners\nof the company he worked for---the Starbucks Coee Company. When Howard Schultz pitched his proposal to the owners of\nStarbucks, the coee shop was hardly a new idea. Arabs began to\nbrew coee six hundred years ago, and the rst European coee\nshop opened its doors in Oxford, England, in 1652 when Isaac\nNewton was ten years old. The cause of the Enlightenment may\nthe Protestant\nhave been\nReformation, but coee was its daily fuel.", "prev_page": {"page_num": 275, "segment_id": "00275"}, "next_page": {"page_num": 277, "segment_id": "00277"}, "flags": {"continuity_gap": true}, "extended_fields": {"has_code": false, "has_formulas": false, "has_diagram": false, "has_list": false, "has_citations": false, "key_terms": ["coee", "espresso", "coeehouses", "starbucks", "schultz", "would", "idea", "owners", "company", "brew"], "content_type": "case_study", "domain": "management|other", "complexity": "intermediate", "companies": ["Starbucks Coee Company"], "people": ["Howard Schultz", "the two owners of 