{"segment_id": "00277", "page_num": 277, "segment": "In England, tea eventually replaced coee as the daytime\nbeverage of choice. London coeehouses gradually disappeared,\nmorphing into private clubs, restaurants, and businesses. Edward\nLloyd’s coeehouse became Lloyds of London and Jonathan’s\ncoeehouse in “Change Alley” became the London Stock Exchange,\nwhere runners are still called “waiters.”\n\nIn the United States, history took a dierent course. The Boston\nTea Party, the Revolution, and the War of 1812 interrupted trade in\ntea, reviving interest in coee. Americans found in coee an\ninexpensive tea substitute that could be drunk in quantity. By 1820,\nthe transition was complete, and the United States became the\nlargest market for coee in the world.\n\nIn the early twentieth century, an alternative to the original\nEthiopian coee tree (arabica) was found in the Congo---the robusta\ncoee plant. The robusta plant grew faster, was more disease\nresistant, was easier to harvest, and contained more caeine. It also\nhad a harsher, less mellow taste. But mixing robusta with arabica\ntook o much of the harsh edge, especially if you added sugar and\ncream. The new inexpensive bean was the key to supercharging the\ngrowing American coee habit. Instant coee was the nal step in\nthe path that took American coee-drinking practices a great\ndistance from their European origins.\n\nWhile Americans were developing robusta and instant coee,\nItalian Luigi Bezzera invented the espresso machine (1901). This\ndevice made a cup of coee by passing hot steam through a charge\nof ground-roasted coee beans. The reaction of the steam and the\ncoee produced a rich, almost syrupy, beverage. The theory was\nthat the quick brewing time prevented the extraction of bitter coee\noils and reduced the amount of caeine. A small porcelain cup of\nItalian espresso has a brown foamy crema on its surface, which fades\nwithin a minute. The crema layer traps aromatics and volatile\navors. The drink could not be easily prepared at home as it needed\nhigh-pressure steam and expensive equipment and was quite labor\nintensive. Italian espresso bars became popular places for a quick\npick-me-up and urban social interaction.", "source_file": "GOOD-STRATEGY-BAD-STRATEGY.pdf", "extraction_method": "pdfminer", "ocr_used": false, "has_table": false, "chapter_num": "1", "chapter_title": ", “Good Strategy Is Unexpected,” and chapter 2,", "section_num": "2.0", "section_title": "businesses. The term “Web 2.0” purportedly referred to a", "l1_summary": "In England, tea eventually replaced coee as the daytime\nbeverage of choice. Americans found in coee an\ninexpensive tea substitute that could be drunk in quantity. By 1820,\nthe transition was complete, and the United States became the\nlargest market for coee in the world.", "l2_summary": "In England, tea eventually replaced coee as the daytime\nbeverage of choice. The Boston\nTea Party, the Revolution, and the War of 1812 interrupted trade in\ntea, reviving interest in coee. Americans found in coee an\ninexpensive tea substitute that could be drunk in quantity. By 1820,\nthe transition was complete, and the United States became the\nlargest market for coee in the world. In the early twentieth century, an alternative to the original\nEthiopian coee tree (arabica) was found in the Congo---the robusta\ncoee plant. This\ndevice made a cup of coee by passing hot steam through a charge\nof ground-roasted coee beans.", "prev_page": {"page_num": 276, "segment_id": "00276"}, "next_page": {"page_num": 278, "segment_id": "00278"}, "flags": {"continuity_gap": true}, "extended_fields": {"has_code": false, "has_formulas": false, "has_diagram": false, "has_list": false, "has_citations": false, "key_terms": ["coee", "became", "robusta", "london", "took", "italian", "espresso", "steam", "beverage", "coeehouse"], "content_type": "reference", "domain": "other", "complexity": "intermediate", "companies": ["Lloyds of London", "Jonathan’s coeeh