{"segment_id": "00281", "page_num": 281, "segment": "We were aware of Starbucks, but you must understand the issue\nof scale. Segafredo supplies over fty thousand dierent cafés\nand restaurants each week. That is a huge volume, and\nStarbucks was quite small. And the large American roasters,\nKraft, Sara Lee, and P&G, were all focused on the mass market.*\nIt was also dicult, from a European perspective, to\nunderstand exactly what Starbucks was. In Europe, coee\nroasters are distinct from restaurants. Although Starbucks was\nknown as a coee company, it was really a retailer. McDonald’s\nis a retailer, but it is never confused with a “beef” company! Yet\nStarbucks was called a “coee company,” and Americans\nseemed to think that its coee was special.\n\nEuropeans see Starbucks as “American coee.” Americans\nthink Starbucks is an Italian espresso bar. But at an Italian\nespresso bar, everyone drinks standing up at the bar; almost\neveryone takes a small cup of pure espresso in a tiny porcelain\ncup. Café-latte is for breakfast only, or for children. There is no\ntakeout; there are no tables. The coee is not a restaurant\nbrand but is supplied by one of the major coee companies, like\nSegafredo. Finally, Italian espresso bars are small family\nbusinesses, not parts of a giant chain.\n\nBy contrast, at Starbucks people drink coee at tables or take\nit out. They drink from paper cups and there is a very long,\ncomplex menu of drinks Europeans have never heard of or\nwanted. The coee is all Starbucks’ own brand and the store is\ncompany owned. And almost all of the drinks are milk based. In\nfact, viewed from Europe, Starbucks is more of a milk company\nthan a coee company and most of its drinks are simply coeeavored milk.\n\nAnd then, Starbucks married together not only coee and\nrestaurants, but also the American penchant for chains and\npublic nancing. It expanded much faster than European\ncompanies. By the time we began to understand Starbucks, it\nwas well established. But you should also understand that\nStarbucks is still a small player in the overall world coee\nbusiness.", "source_file": "GOOD-STRATEGY-BAD-STRATEGY.pdf", "extraction_method": "pdfminer", "ocr_used": false, "has_table": false, "chapter_num": "1", "chapter_title": ", “Good Strategy Is Unexpected,” and chapter 2,", "section_num": "2.0", "section_title": "businesses. The term “Web 2.0” purportedly referred to a", "l1_summary": "Although Starbucks was\nknown as a coee company, it was really a retailer. Yet\nStarbucks was called a “coee company,” and Americans\nseemed to think that its coee was special. Europeans see Starbucks as “American coee.” Americans\nthink Starbucks is an Italian espresso bar.", "l2_summary": "We were aware of Starbucks, but you must understand the issue\nof scale. That is a huge volume, and\nStarbucks was quite small. Although Starbucks was\nknown as a coee company, it was really a retailer. Yet\nStarbucks was called a “coee company,” and Americans\nseemed to think that its coee was special. Europeans see Starbucks as “American coee.” Americans\nthink Starbucks is an Italian espresso bar. The coee is all Starbucks’ own brand and the store is\ncompany owned.", "prev_page": {"page_num": 280, "segment_id": "00280"}, "next_page": {"page_num": 282, "segment_id": "00282"}, "extended_fields": {"has_code": false, "has_formulas": false, "has_diagram": false, "has_list": false, "has_citations": false, "key_terms": ["starbucks", "coee", "company", "understand", "small", "espresso", "drinks", "restaurants", "american", "also"], "content_type": "case_study", "domain": "management", "complexity": "intermediate", "companies": ["Starbucks", "Segafredo", "Kraft", "Sara Lee", "P&G"], "people": [], "products": ["coee", "coffee drinks"], "technologies": [], "frameworks": [], "methodologies": [], "programming_languages": [], "has_best_practices": false, "has_antipatterns": false, "has_instructions": false, "has_metrics": false, "metrics": [], "has_case_study"