{"segment_id": "00282", "page_num": 282, "segment": "Joe Santos’s comments imply that incumbents had diculty\nunderstanding Starbucks because it was vertically integrated---\nbecause it roasted, branded, and served its own coee in its own\ncompany restaurants. Starbucks did not vertically integrate to\npurposefully confuse the competition. It did so in order to be able to\nmutually adjust multiple elements of its business and to capture the\ninformationeach element of its business operations.\n\nIntegration is not always a good idea. When a company can buy\nperfectly good products and services from outside suppliers, it is\nusually wasteful to go through the expense and trouble of mastering\na new set of business operations. However, when the core of a\nbusiness strategy requires the mutual adjustment of multiple\nelements, and especially when there is important learning to be\ncaptured about interactions across business elements, then it may be\nvital to own and control these elements of the business mix.\n\n* The standard date for Newton’s birth is December 25, 1642. However, England’s calendar\n\nat that time was Julian and the Vatican’s was Gregorian. In the Gregorian calendar, Galileo\n\ndied on January 8, 1642, and Newton was born on January 4, 1643, not quite one year\n\nlater.\n\n* Kraft’s main brand was Maxwell House. Sara Lee’s (MJB, Hills Bros., Chase & Sanborn)\n\nwere acquired in 1998 from Nestlé and Café Pilão. P&G’s main brand was Folgers, sold to\n\nSmucker’s in 2008. P&G began to make and market Dunkin’ Donuts brand coee in 2007.", "source_file": "GOOD-STRATEGY-BAD-STRATEGY.pdf", "extraction_method": "pdfminer", "ocr_used": false, "has_table": false, "chapter_num": "1", "chapter_title": ", “Good Strategy Is Unexpected,” and chapter 2,", "section_num": "2.0", "section_title": "businesses. The term “Web 2.0” purportedly referred to a", "l1_summary": "It did so in order to be able to\nmutually adjust multiple elements of its business and to capture the\ninformationeach element of its business operations. However, when the core of a\nbusiness strategy requires the mutual adjustment of multiple\nelements, and especially when there is important...", "l2_summary": "Starbucks did not vertically integrate to\npurposefully confuse the competition. It did so in order to be able to\nmutually adjust multiple elements of its business and to capture the\ninformationeach element of its business operations. However, when the core of a\nbusiness strategy requires the mutual adjustment of multiple\nelements, and especially when there is important learning to be\ncaptured about interactions across business elements, then it may be\nvital to own and control these elements of the business mix. * The standard date for Newton’s birth is December 25, 1642. However, England’s calendar In the Gregorian calendar, Galileo", "prev_page": {"page_num": 281, "segment_id": "00281"}, "next_page": {"page_num": 283, "segment_id": "00283"}, "flags": {"continuity_gap": true}, "extended_fields": {"has_code": false, "has_formulas": false, "has_diagram": false, "has_list": false, "has_citations": false, "key_terms": ["business", "elements", "when", "brand", "starbucks", "because", "vertically", "coee", "company", "multiple"], "content_type": "theory", "domain": "management|architecture", "complexity": "intermediate", "companies": ["Starbucks", "Kraft", "Sara Lee", "Nestlé", "P&G", "Smucker’s"], "people": ["Joe Santos", "Newton", "Galileo"], "products": ["coee", "Maxwell House", "Dunkin’ Donuts brand coee"], "technologies": [], "frameworks": [], "methodologies": [], "programming_languages": [], "has_best_practices": true, "has_antipatterns": false, "has_instructions": false, "has_metrics": false, "metrics": [], "has_case_study": false, "case_study_company": null, "tools_mentioned": [], "topics": ["vertical integration", "Starbucks business model", "company strategy"], "key_concepts": ["vertical integration", "mutual adjustment of business elements", "l