ppening again. Real estate prices were soaring and\ntoo much easy credit was being extended on all fronts.\n\nThe outside view of the situation was hardly complex. The\ninternational evidence is clear---sharp economic problems following", "source_file": "GOOD-STRATEGY-BAD-STRATEGY.pdf", "extraction_method": "pdfminer", "ocr_used": false, "has_table": false, "chapter_num": "1", "chapter_title": ", “Good Strategy Is Unexpected,” and chapter 2,", "section_num": "2.0", "section_title": "businesses. The term “Web 2.0” purportedly referred to a", "l1_summary": "The fourth and fth problems---social herding and the inside view\n---deserve special attention, especially with regard to the 2008\nnancial crisis. Both\nvirtues help mitigate the bias inherent in social herding and the\ninside view. The outside view of the situation was hardly complex.", "l2_summary": "ignore related pertinent data---to believe that “this case is\ndierent.”7 The fourth and fth problems---social herding and the inside view\n---deserve special attention, especially with regard to the 2008\nnancial crisis. Both\nvirtues help mitigate the bias inherent in social herding and the\ninside view. The inside view describes the fact that people tend to see\nthemselves, their group, their project, their company, or their nation\nas special and dierent. Secondly, there was the belief that the Federal Reserve’s\nexpertise at managing interest rates had eliminated the risk of major\neconomic swings---that times had changed. The outside view of the situation was hardly complex.", "prev_page": {"page_num": 317, "segment_id": "00317"}, "next_page": {"page_num": 319, "segment_id": "00319"}, "flags": {"continuity_gap": true}, "extended_fields": {"has_code": false, "has_formulas": false, "has_diagram": false, "has_list": false, "has_citations": false, "key_terms": ["view", "inside", "economic", "belief", "dierent", "nancial", "situation", "risk", "times", "there"], "content_type": "theory", "domain": "management", "co